Commands
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Usage
-----

 You should use ( Include "BlitzLibs:dbp.bb) at the start of your code
 and then all the Below commands should work.. 

See The Example Player included in this archive.

DBMLoad{"MoD Name"}
-------------------

Load DBM Mod to Memory

ClearMem{}
----------

Removes Load DBM from memory 
	- Can be called straight affter PlayDBM
	- Should Be Used Before Loading new mod or quiting Program.

PlayDBM{AudioMode,AudioFreq}
----------------------------

Play a DBM Which has been loaded in to memory. 

Returns 0 if all is ok or ......

	1 - DBM is all ready Playing 
	2 - Not Enough Memory
	3 - DBM Module Truncated
	4 - Not a DBM Module
	5 - AHI ASL ERROR

AudioMode - AHI Audio Mode 
AudioFreq - AHI Frequence 

StopDBM{}
---------

Stop A DBM Playing

DBMVolume{vol}
--------------

Set Volume  (0 - 64)

SetPosition{song,pat}
---------------------

Start Playing DBM Mod At Set Song & Position 

WaitPosition{songpoz,patpoz}
----------------------------

Check if replayer is at given position

	Returns TRUE if replayer plays pattern (SongPos) that 
	is equal or greater than given value, and position in this 
	pattern is greater or equal than given value(PattPos).Otherwise 
	it returns FALSE.

G7Command{}
-----------

	This functions returns value that was used in last 7xx command.
	You can use this function just like the old E8x command from
	protracker.

GTModuleAttr{Tags}
------------------

		This function will give you some info about currently
		played module.
		
		Currently, one or more of this tags can be used
		with this function:


	InstNum
	-------

		Number of instruments in module

	PattNum
	-------

		Number of patterns in module.

	ChanNum
	-------

		Number of channels that module is using.

	ModName
	-------

		Module name.

	InstNames
	---------

		Instruments names.

NOTE - The above commands have not been tested and may not work with
       all mods.

